#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:219
msgid "Possible future unreservations"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:221
msgid "`unsized`"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:223
msgid ""
"This would be a modifier on types, but we already have `<T: ?Sized>` and we "
"could have `T: !Sized` so there seems to be no need for keeping `unsized`."
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:226
msgid ""
"However, `unsized type` or `unsized struct` might be a desirable syntax for "
"declaring a _dynamically sized type (DST)_ or completely unsized type. "
"Therefore, we will hold off on unreserving `unsized` until we have a better "
"ideas of how custom DSTs will work and it's clear we don't need `unsized` as "
"a keyword."
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:232
msgid "`priv`"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:234
msgid ""
"Here, `priv` is a privacy / visibility modifier on things like fields, and "
"items. An example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:244
msgid ""
"Since fields are already private by default, `priv` would only be an extra "
"hint that users can use to be more explicit, but serves no other purpose. "
"Note however that `enum` variants are not private by default. Neither are "
"items in `trait`s. Annotating items as `priv` in traits could potentially be "
"useful for internal `fn`s used in provided `fn` implementations. However, we "
"could possibly use `pub(self)` instead of `priv`."
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:252
msgid ""
"Permitting `priv` could also be confusing for readers. Consider for example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:261
msgid ""
"An unsuspecting reader can get the impression that `bar` is private but "
"`baz` is public. We could of course lint against this mixing, but it does "
"not seem worth the complexity."
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:265
msgid ""
"However, right now (2018-04-26), there is a lot of movement around the "
"module system. So we would like to wait and discuss unreserving this keyword "
"at some later time."
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:269
msgid "`box`"
msgstr ""

#: src/2421-unreservations-2018.md:271
msgid ""
"We use this in nightly for box patterns. We might want to unreserve this "
"eventually however."
msgstr ""

